WEBVTT

00:04.569 --> 00:07.616
[gunfire]DANNY:
My name is Danny McNamara.

00:07.659 --> 00:09.052
I used to work for the FBI.

00:09.096 --> 00:10.923
LEXI:
And I'm Lexi Vaziri.

00:10.967 --> 00:12.490
I used to be a thief.

00:12.534 --> 00:14.579
DANNY:
Excuse me, a master thief.

00:14.623 --> 00:16.929
We're back on the hunt
after the Vatican

00:16.973 --> 00:18.801
was attacked
by a mysterious group

00:18.844 --> 00:21.804
led by someone who calls himself
the Great Khan.

00:21.847 --> 00:24.198
LEXI:
He's looking for
an ancient Mongolian artifact

00:24.241 --> 00:28.071
called the Spirit Banner.DANNY: Also known
as the Soul of Genghis Khan.

00:28.115 --> 00:30.247
And they're leaving
a path of destruction

00:30.291 --> 00:32.293
in their wake
to get their hands on it.

00:33.685 --> 00:35.644
LEXI:
So, it looks like it's up to us
to stop them

00:35.687 --> 00:37.080
by finding the Banner.

00:38.125 --> 00:39.909
DANNY:
Before they do.

00:41.954 --> 00:43.869
Previously
onBlood & Treasure...

00:43.913 --> 00:45.654
I can find you the Banner.

00:45.697 --> 00:47.438
LEXI:
And who do we talk to?

00:47.482 --> 00:49.571
HARDWICK:
Former member
of the Night Devils,

00:49.614 --> 00:51.051
Andrei Levchenko.

00:51.094 --> 00:52.835
LEVCHENKO:
My grandfather told me

00:52.878 --> 00:54.880
that Stalin would appropriate
the strangest antiquities

00:54.924 --> 00:56.839
and send them somewhere
far away to be studied.

00:56.882 --> 00:58.145
You know
where the Banner went.

00:58.188 --> 01:00.234
Have you ever heard
of the forbidden zone?

01:00.277 --> 01:02.845
It's a remote region in
Mongolia rumored to be

01:02.888 --> 01:04.455
the burial place
of Genghis Khan.

01:04.499 --> 01:06.283
Like America's Area 51.

01:06.327 --> 01:07.632
[Claudine screams]

01:07.676 --> 01:10.287
Claudine. Claudine!

01:10.331 --> 01:11.984
I'm going with you
to Mongolia,

01:12.028 --> 01:13.638
and I will draw him out
and kill him.

01:13.682 --> 01:16.032
KATE:Chuck, we're on
the same side here.

01:16.076 --> 01:18.382
You want justice
for the people he's murdered?

01:18.426 --> 01:19.731
Let's work together.

01:19.775 --> 01:21.298
You think

01:21.342 --> 01:24.084
that everyone in your life
is bound to let you down

01:24.127 --> 01:26.260
or-or betray you,

01:26.303 --> 01:27.913
and you cannot wait for me

01:27.957 --> 01:29.219
to prove you right.

01:32.918 --> 01:34.964
♪

01:55.419 --> 01:56.725
It was Claudine's.

01:56.768 --> 01:58.205
It's beautiful.

01:58.248 --> 02:01.686
I told her I loved her
every hour of every day,

02:01.730 --> 02:03.340
and yet I did not say it enough.

02:03.384 --> 02:05.951
You must tell each other
every minute of your love.

02:07.823 --> 02:10.304
Oh, definitely.You know,

02:10.347 --> 02:12.654
every couple has their own way
of speaking their feelings.

02:12.697 --> 02:14.830
There is love,
and there is not love.

02:14.873 --> 02:17.224
Um, no. You can have
the feelings

02:17.267 --> 02:19.182
without expressing them.LEVCHENKO:
When one of you

02:19.226 --> 02:21.663
loses the other, you will see.

02:26.494 --> 02:29.105
He invades my country,
kills my Claudine.

02:29.149 --> 02:31.803
And yet no one can find
this Great Khan?DANNY: Levchenko.

02:31.847 --> 02:34.241
Trust me,
we want him as much as you do.

02:34.284 --> 02:36.634
Just take us
to the secret Soviet base.

02:36.678 --> 02:38.636
We'll find
the Spirit Banner he's after.

02:38.680 --> 02:40.856
We'll catch the Great Khan.

02:40.899 --> 02:43.467
[radio static crackles]

02:43.511 --> 02:45.077
We are beyond

02:45.121 --> 02:47.297
where modern technology
can reach us now.

02:48.820 --> 02:50.866
♪

03:09.276 --> 03:10.712
[indistinct chatter]

03:13.105 --> 03:15.064
This is it.

03:15.107 --> 03:16.631
The forbidden zone.

03:16.674 --> 03:19.155
The Mongolians
declared this land sacred.

03:19.199 --> 03:21.070
Legend says

03:21.113 --> 03:24.552
it's the final resting place
of Genghis Khan himself.

03:24.595 --> 03:28.251
No outsiders allowed
under penalty of death.

03:28.295 --> 03:31.515
Just the spot
for a supersecret Soviet base.

03:31.559 --> 03:34.388
And a huge insult to the locals
for Russia to have built here.

03:34.431 --> 03:36.564
LEVCHENKO:
Come on, the Mongols started it.

03:36.607 --> 03:38.435
What? My grandfather
told me stories

03:38.479 --> 03:40.350
about the Khans
trying to invade Russia,

03:40.394 --> 03:42.874
but we fought them back.DANNY:
The Battle of Kalka River.

03:42.918 --> 03:44.267
A Russian victory,

03:44.311 --> 03:45.529
except it was a trap.

03:45.573 --> 03:46.791
The Khan's army
faked retreat,

03:46.835 --> 03:48.445
and when the
Russians gave chase,

03:48.489 --> 03:50.055
the Mongols were there
to slaughter them.

03:50.099 --> 03:52.232
You think all
Russians are fools?

03:55.235 --> 03:57.846
We all know every culture
tells its own lies.

03:57.889 --> 03:59.891
Remember,

03:59.935 --> 04:02.938
I need you alive.
They don't.

04:02.981 --> 04:06.028
Maybe less history
lectures that piss off

04:06.071 --> 04:08.030
the angry motorcycle
gang bent on revenge.

04:08.073 --> 04:09.945
Hmm.Okay?

04:13.470 --> 04:16.865
Let's all merrily
press on, shall we?

04:18.649 --> 04:19.998
[grunts]

04:20.999 --> 04:24.089
That pendant was worth
£200,000 at least.

04:24.133 --> 04:26.309
It was his last connection
to her.

04:26.353 --> 04:29.617
Not a great sign
of his mental state.

04:29.660 --> 04:32.054
I can't even imagine
what I would do

04:32.097 --> 04:35.405
if I lost you.Let's just not.

04:35.449 --> 04:36.624
LEVCHENKO:
So,

04:36.667 --> 04:38.060
lead the way to the base.

04:38.103 --> 04:39.844
What?

04:39.888 --> 04:41.977
You said your grandfather
brought you here.LEVCHENKO: Yes,

04:42.020 --> 04:43.326
he brought me here.

04:43.370 --> 04:44.719
Then he pointed at the mountains

04:44.762 --> 04:46.851
and said the base
is somewhere up there.

04:46.895 --> 04:49.332
If I knew how to get
to the base itself,

04:49.376 --> 04:52.379
I wouldn't need you, genius.

05:00.909 --> 05:02.737
♪ Girl, you're with me

05:02.780 --> 05:04.782
♪ No matter where I go now...

05:04.826 --> 05:06.697
You're not adding enough water.

05:06.741 --> 05:08.264
No water in a manhattan.

05:08.308 --> 05:11.006
There is
when Shaw makes them.

05:11.049 --> 05:13.530
If he wants me to cover,
I'm running an honest bar.

05:13.574 --> 05:15.184
Where is he, anyway?

05:15.227 --> 05:17.012
He's helping me
with a job.

05:17.055 --> 05:18.535
Some light undercover work.

05:18.579 --> 05:20.885
He needs the break.
He was super bummed out

05:20.929 --> 05:25.237
because the CIA lady said
he was the loser of his family.

05:25.281 --> 05:27.588
Hey, she didn't use
the word "loser."

05:27.631 --> 05:29.764
How'd you hear what
the CIA lady said?

05:29.807 --> 05:33.158
You put your ear up to the vent,
you can hear everything

05:33.202 --> 05:34.246
in this place.

05:34.290 --> 05:35.552
Is it true

05:35.596 --> 05:37.641
he can't go back to America?

05:37.685 --> 05:39.513
I hope so.

05:39.556 --> 05:41.515
I need this place.

05:41.558 --> 05:42.907
Don't you have a home
or something?

05:42.951 --> 05:46.171
My living situation
is complicated.

05:46.215 --> 05:48.391
Well, he's not lying.
I'm his uncle,

05:48.435 --> 05:50.262
and my sister is crazy.

05:50.306 --> 05:52.308
Want to talk about it?

05:52.352 --> 05:54.919
You're really embracing
this "being a bartender" thing.

05:54.963 --> 05:57.008
You know, it's great.

05:57.052 --> 05:59.924
It's like being a priest
but with a lot more booze.

06:01.186 --> 06:03.406
All right,
the exact same amount of booze.

06:03.450 --> 06:05.060
[phone vibrates]

06:10.674 --> 06:12.154
Trouble, Padre?

06:12.197 --> 06:13.982
Yeah. I think

06:14.025 --> 06:17.551
this might be
our not-so-secret CIA friend

06:17.594 --> 06:19.248
reaching out.

06:19.291 --> 06:22.077
How'd you two leave things?Kate suspects

06:22.120 --> 06:25.428
that the Great Khan's plan
is connected to the Vatican.

06:25.472 --> 06:27.430
She wants me to help
her figure out how.

06:27.474 --> 06:29.563
Well, I know that park.
Nice and quiet.

06:29.606 --> 06:31.521
Perfect place for a meet.

06:31.565 --> 06:33.958
Congrats
on becoming a CIA asset.

06:34.002 --> 06:36.265
Uh, no. We are having
a conversation.

06:36.308 --> 06:37.701
She knows you're here.

06:37.745 --> 06:39.355
If she wanted to talk,
she'd come to you.

06:39.399 --> 06:41.401
She doesn't think it's safe.

06:41.444 --> 06:43.446
Is...

06:45.013 --> 06:46.971
Is it not safe?

06:47.015 --> 06:49.321
Look, she probably thinks
this place is being watched,

06:49.365 --> 06:51.106
so she wants to meet you
somewhere else

06:51.149 --> 06:52.455
to give you something.

06:52.499 --> 06:53.804
Give me something?Mm-hmm.

06:53.848 --> 06:55.371
Like microfilm?

06:55.415 --> 06:58.809
Chuck, you live in a world
where people text.

06:58.853 --> 07:01.159
Right.We're way past microfilm.

07:01.203 --> 07:04.206
Should I... I should...
I should text her back, right?

07:04.249 --> 07:06.904
Should... Are there emojis
for this kind of thing?

07:06.948 --> 07:08.558
First rule of the spy game is...Yeah?

07:08.602 --> 07:10.212
...don't involve other people.

07:10.255 --> 07:12.432
Goes nicely
with my first rule,

07:12.475 --> 07:14.912
don't get involved
with spies.

07:24.226 --> 07:27.359
MAN:
Hardwick, you've got a visitor.

07:30.841 --> 07:33.017
May I have a word, Mr. Hardwick?

07:33.061 --> 07:36.238
The truth is we don't
normally get many visitors.

07:37.195 --> 07:40.503
Although I'm happy to say
that's taken a delightful turn

07:40.547 --> 07:43.550
ever since a new kingpin
calling himself the Great Khan

07:43.593 --> 07:45.639
started stirring up the pot.

07:45.682 --> 07:47.510
I've come to offer you a job.

07:47.554 --> 07:50.470
Look, I don't mean to be
rude. Maybe you've noticed

07:50.513 --> 07:51.993
I'm otherwise engaged.

07:52.036 --> 07:54.256
Possibly for the rest
of my natural life.

07:54.299 --> 07:57.128
Do you accept my offer
of employment?

07:59.130 --> 08:01.089
Uh...

08:01.132 --> 08:02.786
Yeah.

08:02.830 --> 08:05.180
Yeah, I do. I accept.
Whatever. Why not?

08:06.355 --> 08:09.097
[phone beeps][explosion]

08:09.140 --> 08:10.925
[alarm blaring]Oh, my God.

08:10.968 --> 08:12.796
[indistinct shouting]

08:12.840 --> 08:14.755
This is like
a genuine prison break.

08:14.798 --> 08:17.235
[chuckles]:
What are you gonna do? Like,

08:17.279 --> 08:19.063
march me
right out the front door?

08:19.107 --> 08:20.325
Not exactly.

08:25.679 --> 08:27.724
♪

08:45.612 --> 08:47.309
Can you find this base or not?

08:47.352 --> 08:49.964
You are the
so-called expert.

08:50.007 --> 08:53.576
Okay. Okay, I, uh,
think I got an idea.

08:53.620 --> 08:56.100
I just need an antenna.

08:57.232 --> 09:00.191
VALENTIN: Hey!We need him to find the base.

09:00.235 --> 09:01.671
He needs an antenna.

09:01.715 --> 09:03.281
Problem solved.

09:03.325 --> 09:04.674
Whatever he does next,

09:04.718 --> 09:07.024
I advise you
to make it successful.

09:09.200 --> 09:10.767
[grunts]

09:10.811 --> 09:11.986
Here.

09:12.029 --> 09:13.727
Thanks.

09:17.557 --> 09:19.689
[Danny grunts]

09:19.733 --> 09:21.909
LEXI:
You seem fairly confident.

09:21.952 --> 09:23.432
I'm assuming you
have a good plan?

09:23.475 --> 09:24.825
I have aplan.

09:24.868 --> 09:26.653
We'll see
if it's a good one.

09:26.696 --> 09:28.480
During the Cold War,

09:28.524 --> 09:31.092
the Soviets
would broadcast coded messages

09:31.135 --> 09:32.833
from secret outposts
like this one.

09:32.876 --> 09:35.183
They were powered
to broadcast on their own

09:35.226 --> 09:36.706
for a hundred years in the event

09:36.750 --> 09:38.186
of a nuclear war.

09:38.229 --> 09:39.927
Ham operators
call them Ghost Signals.

09:39.970 --> 09:42.582
Shortwave radios
can still pick them up

09:42.625 --> 09:44.932
if we're close enough
to the source.Well,

09:44.975 --> 09:47.108
that Russian is still
very angry about his car.

09:47.151 --> 09:48.675
Well, I didn't tell you
to tear off the antenna.

09:48.718 --> 09:50.851
Well, excuse me for
answering to your needs

09:50.894 --> 09:53.070
so quickly. Won't
happen again next time.

09:53.114 --> 09:55.246
Particularly if
we die out here.

09:55.290 --> 09:57.597
Okay.[sighs]

09:57.640 --> 09:59.555
[buzzing]

10:00.512 --> 10:03.385
Just... give it a minute, okay?

10:03.428 --> 10:05.169
[static crackling][man speaking indistinctly
over radio]

10:12.220 --> 10:14.614
[man speaking Russian
over radio][gasps]

10:14.657 --> 10:15.963
And voilà.

10:16.006 --> 10:17.573
See, he found it.

10:17.617 --> 10:20.315
Never doubted you
for a minute.

10:20.358 --> 10:22.665
We follow this
right to the base.

10:22.709 --> 10:24.362
LEXI:
Thank God for the paranoia

10:24.406 --> 10:25.929
of a nuclear war.

10:25.973 --> 10:28.758
Okay, let's go.

10:28.802 --> 10:30.847
[speaking Russian]

10:31.935 --> 10:33.502
[chuckles]

10:33.545 --> 10:35.809
How's your Russian?Pretty rusty.

10:35.852 --> 10:38.246
But I think he said
we'll soon be joining

10:38.289 --> 10:40.944
his wife, Claudine.
Maybe it's Russian slang.

10:40.988 --> 10:42.511
On the off chance it's not,

10:42.554 --> 10:44.818
first chance we get
to escape with the Banner?

10:44.861 --> 10:46.820
We're taking it.

10:46.863 --> 10:48.952
♪

11:20.418 --> 11:22.464
♪

11:24.596 --> 11:26.729
[man speaking Russian
over radio]

11:26.773 --> 11:28.731
Stop!

11:28.775 --> 11:30.559
[brakes screech]

11:30.602 --> 11:32.169
LEVCHENKO:
Why are we stopping?

11:32.213 --> 11:33.693
Are you lost?

11:33.736 --> 11:35.346
[man speaking Russian]

11:35.390 --> 11:37.348
[Night Devils laughing]

11:37.392 --> 11:39.742
He say your signal is weak.

11:39.786 --> 11:42.658
His signal is fine.

11:46.227 --> 11:47.750
Hey.

11:47.794 --> 11:49.970
Your signal's fine, right?Yes.

11:50.013 --> 11:52.015
We're stopping because of these.

11:52.059 --> 11:53.800
Mongolian deer stones.

11:53.843 --> 11:56.324
Some of these could date back
to the Bronze Age.

11:56.367 --> 11:58.630
We can't drive through.

12:01.329 --> 12:04.071
Hey! This is sacred ground!

12:04.114 --> 12:06.377
Sacred to Mongolians,
not to Russians.

12:06.421 --> 12:07.814
Maybe I just run you over,

12:07.857 --> 12:09.511
keep the Banner for myself.

12:09.554 --> 12:12.427
Gentlemen, you would not have
gotten this far without him,

12:12.470 --> 12:15.125
and you know it.You want the Banner?

12:15.169 --> 12:17.084
You want the Khan?

12:17.127 --> 12:20.348
You run me over,
you get nothing.

12:22.350 --> 12:25.135
A hike
will do my aching heart good.

12:27.572 --> 12:29.096
So, how does it feel

12:29.139 --> 12:31.838
to be with a man who declares
his love for stones

12:31.881 --> 12:33.361
more than he does for you?

12:33.404 --> 12:35.885
DANNY:
Help me put this back.Okay.

12:37.321 --> 12:38.670
I don't care if he's grieving.

12:38.714 --> 12:40.411
He is a jackass.Yeah.

12:40.455 --> 12:42.718
Who is he to judge us?Just because we don't

12:42.762 --> 12:44.894
word vomit those
three magical words.

12:44.938 --> 12:47.418
Please, we're
people of action.[grunts]

12:47.462 --> 12:49.725
Whenever you say it,
bad things happen.

12:49.769 --> 12:51.901
People betray you.Or die.

12:51.945 --> 12:53.033
Every time.Every time.

12:53.076 --> 12:55.078
LEVCHENKO:
American!

12:56.427 --> 12:58.081
I found the base!

12:58.125 --> 13:00.170
This guy...

13:06.960 --> 13:09.005
♪

13:31.288 --> 13:33.073
What does that say?

13:33.116 --> 13:35.292
"Semenovodcheskaja
Stantsyia."

13:35.336 --> 13:37.729
It means "Seed House."

13:37.773 --> 13:40.036
This does not
look promising.

13:40.080 --> 13:41.995
I disagree.

13:42.038 --> 13:44.301
Seeds bear fruit.

13:44.345 --> 13:47.870
I don't want fruit.
I want the Banner.

13:47.914 --> 13:50.481
[electricity zapping]

13:50.525 --> 13:52.440
♪

14:18.727 --> 14:20.772
♪

14:29.129 --> 14:31.174
Lovely day.

14:34.395 --> 14:36.049
So, are you, like,
a go-between?

14:36.092 --> 14:37.746
Like, you're gonna tell me
where to go next?

14:40.009 --> 14:41.489
Was I supposed to
get a code word?

14:41.532 --> 14:43.012
I never got a code word.

14:44.448 --> 14:47.103
You don't speak English.

14:47.147 --> 14:49.236
You are not a spy.

14:49.279 --> 14:51.238
You are just a nice
old man having

14:51.281 --> 14:54.763
his day in the park ruined
by a crazy, babbling foreigner.

14:56.765 --> 14:59.376
That seems correct.

14:59.420 --> 15:01.204
Good job, Chuck.

15:01.248 --> 15:02.249
You're early.

15:02.292 --> 15:04.294
[exhales]

15:04.338 --> 15:06.209
Oh, yeah. Yeah,
I was just, uh,

15:06.253 --> 15:08.298
clearing that
innocent bystander.

15:08.342 --> 15:10.910
I knew you'd come
by yourself.

15:10.953 --> 15:12.824
Eyes forward.

15:15.305 --> 15:16.916
What are you doing here?

15:16.959 --> 15:18.613
Are you in danger?

15:18.656 --> 15:20.310
Wait, are... Am I in danger?

15:20.354 --> 15:22.965
Chuck, please just
shut up and listen.

15:23.009 --> 15:25.272
Whatever the Great Khan stole
from the Vatican,

15:25.315 --> 15:28.014
it was connected to the trail
of the Spirit Banner.

15:29.015 --> 15:30.842
Found something
you need to see.

15:32.844 --> 15:34.846
Did you...

15:34.890 --> 15:37.588
Did you put a code
in the crossword puzzle?

15:39.155 --> 15:41.462
There's a thumb drive
in the newspaper.

15:41.505 --> 15:42.985
Oh, okay.

15:43.029 --> 15:44.465
How would I have time

15:44.508 --> 15:45.945
to print up an entire...?Right, I...

15:45.988 --> 15:47.250
I made a terrible mistake.You're right. No.

15:47.294 --> 15:48.295
You're right. It's...

15:48.338 --> 15:50.775
That was a dumb idea.

15:51.776 --> 15:53.865
I can't access the places

15:53.909 --> 15:55.650
you can at the Vatican.

15:55.693 --> 15:57.086
It's up to you to find out

15:57.130 --> 15:58.566
what the letter on
the thumb drive means.

15:58.609 --> 16:00.002
All right.

16:01.438 --> 16:04.006
But you have to understand,
Chuck.

16:04.050 --> 16:07.531
Once you go down this path,
there's no turning back.

16:07.575 --> 16:09.838
Whatever we find.

16:09.881 --> 16:11.883
You've chosen a side now.

16:11.927 --> 16:13.711
Yeah.

16:13.755 --> 16:16.236
I understand.

16:17.672 --> 16:19.587
Okay.

16:19.630 --> 16:21.241
I'll reach out again soon.

16:25.593 --> 16:28.639
[exhales]

16:34.776 --> 16:36.778
Gonna need this.

16:45.395 --> 16:46.962
Oh.

16:47.006 --> 16:50.052
I know why the Russians
lost the Cold War.

16:50.096 --> 16:52.794
They spent all their money on
paintings of Stalin everywhere.

16:52.837 --> 16:54.883
Russians do not lose wars

16:54.926 --> 16:56.537
because we never stop
fighting them.

16:58.104 --> 16:59.757
The Banner.

17:00.715 --> 17:02.760
DANNY:
It did come here.

17:02.804 --> 17:04.414
So where is it, then?

17:07.678 --> 17:11.030
What kind of military base
is this?

17:14.642 --> 17:17.079
This isn't a military base.

17:17.123 --> 17:19.168
It's a lab.

17:22.128 --> 17:24.913
Why build a botanical lab
all the way out here?

17:24.956 --> 17:27.916
DANNY:
Soviet scientists
were fighting a losing war

17:27.959 --> 17:31.224
against crop failure
and famine, helped along

17:31.267 --> 17:33.443
by their own
failed experiments.

17:40.102 --> 17:42.278
DANNY:
Growing and protecting food

17:42.322 --> 17:44.628
became a matter of
national security.

17:44.672 --> 17:47.196
While millions of Russians
starved to death.

17:47.240 --> 17:49.503
Led by so-called experts
like you.

17:49.546 --> 17:52.027
The problem started
because of Stalin,

17:52.071 --> 17:54.682
best friend of
your grandfather.

17:54.725 --> 17:57.902
LEXI:
Hey, Daniel?

17:57.946 --> 17:59.469
We've got a banner to find

17:59.513 --> 18:02.211
and yet another creepy room
to explore.

18:08.739 --> 18:10.524
[Lexi coughs]

18:12.482 --> 18:14.180
Delightful.

18:28.672 --> 18:32.285
This clearly wasn't
just a botanical lab.

18:32.328 --> 18:34.200
DANNY:
Yeah, when their
crop genetics failed,

18:34.243 --> 18:37.159
the Soviets turned
to all kinds of pseudoscience.

18:37.203 --> 18:40.771
They had no idea
what was even possible.

18:40.815 --> 18:43.296
We have always done
what it takes to survive.

18:43.339 --> 18:45.515
These scientists wanted

18:45.559 --> 18:47.604
more than just to survive.

18:57.658 --> 18:59.703
[man speaking Russian
over radio]

19:11.019 --> 19:12.977
The Banner was in the picture.

19:13.021 --> 19:14.849
It washere.

19:14.892 --> 19:17.852
Now there's nothing
left here but garbage!

19:18.853 --> 19:21.421
DANNY: Look, we can
find where it went.

19:21.464 --> 19:24.206
If they transported something
this important anywhere else,

19:24.250 --> 19:25.860
the records would show it.

19:33.868 --> 19:35.130
[gun clicks]

19:35.174 --> 19:36.740
Did you find the Banner?

19:36.784 --> 19:40.179
Banner. Sorry, which
banner was that?

19:40.222 --> 19:41.919
[horse approaches]

19:43.617 --> 19:45.793
[grunting]

19:45.836 --> 19:47.055
[arm cracks]

19:53.235 --> 19:55.455
I take it you two
didn't come together.

19:56.586 --> 19:58.675
Must be my guardian angel, then.

19:58.719 --> 19:59.981
Get up.

20:00.024 --> 20:03.593
Let's go for a little stroll,
shall we?

20:09.425 --> 20:10.644
Levchenko,

20:10.687 --> 20:12.646
translate this for me.

20:12.689 --> 20:15.214
Please.

20:16.258 --> 20:18.652
LEVCHENKO:
Something about...

20:19.609 --> 20:21.524
...animal experiments.
I don't know.

20:31.447 --> 20:33.275
What about this man?

20:33.319 --> 20:35.016
What does it say
he was doing

20:35.059 --> 20:36.757
with the Banner?LEVCHENKO:
Uh...

20:36.800 --> 20:38.280
Nothing. No, no.

20:38.324 --> 20:40.761
No, this is all
about... hair.

20:40.804 --> 20:42.197
What do you mean, hair?

20:42.241 --> 20:43.677
Horsehair?

20:43.720 --> 20:45.244
Yes. Why?

20:45.287 --> 20:46.462
The Spirit Banners
were made

20:46.506 --> 20:47.768
out of the hair
of the favorite horse

20:47.811 --> 20:49.639
of the man who carried it.

20:49.683 --> 20:51.641
It says they clipped
some of the hair

20:51.685 --> 20:53.730
from the Banner
looking for elements

20:53.774 --> 20:55.210
of a man.

20:55.254 --> 20:57.517
Someone they call Temuüjin.

20:57.560 --> 21:00.911
That's Genghis Khan's
birth name.

21:02.957 --> 21:06.221
After that, uh, it's all
about some kind of code.

21:06.265 --> 21:09.442
Cracking the life code.
Something like this.

21:09.485 --> 21:11.705
It's what
they used to call DNA.

21:11.748 --> 21:15.143
Scientists were just starting
to understand that in the '60s.

21:15.186 --> 21:17.972
That's why the
Banner was here.

21:18.015 --> 21:19.321
They were trying to capture

21:19.365 --> 21:21.889
the original Khan's
genetic material.

21:22.890 --> 21:24.500
[door opens]

21:25.501 --> 21:28.112
[grunting, panting]

21:28.156 --> 21:29.984
Found him outside.

21:30.027 --> 21:31.942
Tracking us.

21:31.986 --> 21:33.596
He wasn't the only one.

21:33.640 --> 21:34.945
Someone else is out there.

21:34.989 --> 21:36.991
I don't think
they're with the Khan.

21:37.034 --> 21:40.299
Well, one threat to our lives
at a time, I guess.

21:41.952 --> 21:43.302
You're welcome.

21:43.345 --> 21:44.955
Who is he?

21:48.872 --> 21:50.178
He works for the Great Khan.

21:51.832 --> 21:53.573
Are you the one
who killed my Claudine?

21:53.616 --> 21:55.444
Wait! We need him alive.

21:55.488 --> 21:57.141
He could have information
on the Khan.

21:57.185 --> 21:59.579
He'll speak faster
after I blow out his kneecaps.

21:59.622 --> 22:02.233
There is nothing you can do
to me that would be worse

22:02.277 --> 22:04.801
than what the Great Khan would
if I betrayed him.

22:05.802 --> 22:07.456
Check his pockets.

22:08.849 --> 22:10.372
Tell me what the Khan
is planning.

22:10.416 --> 22:12.592
Why does he want
the Spirit Banner?

22:12.635 --> 22:15.072
When he gets the Soul,
you'll see.

22:15.116 --> 22:18.728
He'll... He'll bring
the world to its knees.

22:19.990 --> 22:22.602
It's too late for you.

22:22.645 --> 22:23.777
The Khan's men are coming.

22:35.745 --> 22:38.574
[helicopter blades whirring]That doesn't sound
very welcoming.

22:38.618 --> 22:40.968
Let them come. We are ready.

22:41.011 --> 22:43.753
We'll be outnumbered
and outgunned.

22:43.797 --> 22:46.147
No, we know the
layout of the base.

22:46.190 --> 22:47.757
They don't.

22:47.801 --> 22:49.629
We draw them in,

22:49.672 --> 22:52.153
let them think
they've caught us off guard.

22:53.459 --> 22:55.417
Then we use
the bottlenecks of the base

22:55.461 --> 22:57.376
to turn their numbers
against them.

22:57.419 --> 22:59.465
We've got fertilizer,
gasoline.

22:59.508 --> 23:01.989
Yeah. We can do this.

23:02.032 --> 23:04.861
Hey. You want any of your guys
to survive,

23:04.905 --> 23:06.341
you've got to listen to me.

23:06.385 --> 23:08.299
If only to avenge my Claudine.

23:09.300 --> 23:10.563
Give him a gun.

23:15.524 --> 23:17.700
Let's get ready.

23:28.624 --> 23:30.626
[gasps]

23:30.670 --> 23:32.715
[ice clinks]

23:46.816 --> 23:48.557
Am I dead?

23:48.601 --> 23:50.777
BATU:
As a matter of fact, you are.

23:50.820 --> 23:52.648
You were
beaten unrecognizable.

23:52.692 --> 23:56.217
Body burned.
Thrown into an incinerator.

23:56.260 --> 23:59.046
A quick disposal
of any evidence

23:59.089 --> 24:02.136
from the worst prison riot
in Ireland's history.

24:03.093 --> 24:05.966
It'll be a week before
they realize what's happened.

24:06.009 --> 24:08.969
What do you want with me?Mr. Hardwick,

24:09.012 --> 24:11.798
I want to put you to work.

24:13.582 --> 24:16.019
Thank you.

24:16.063 --> 24:18.979
[chuckles]Gin and tonic.

24:19.022 --> 24:21.460
London dry, of course.

24:24.463 --> 24:26.726
[exhales]

24:26.769 --> 24:28.728
Cheers.

24:28.771 --> 24:31.295
[chuckles]
I-I don't know what to say.

24:31.339 --> 24:33.559
Thank you. Uh...
[sniffles]

24:33.602 --> 24:35.865
Well, you've obviously done
your homework on me.

24:35.909 --> 24:37.388
It's just I, uh...

24:37.432 --> 24:40.957
I know next to nothing
about you, so, um...

24:44.134 --> 24:45.571
Thank you.

24:45.614 --> 24:47.616
It strikes me you were
able to break me out

24:47.660 --> 24:49.705
of a maximum
security prison

24:49.749 --> 24:51.881
in broad daylight--
that's no mean feat--

24:51.925 --> 24:54.405
while somebody killed my father
in another.

24:54.449 --> 24:56.712
So, one might be inclined
to think

24:56.756 --> 25:00.150
that his job offer
wasn't as well received as mine.

25:00.194 --> 25:03.371
Considering the day before
you broke me out of prison,

25:03.414 --> 25:06.287
I got a visit from a certain
Danny McNamara and Lexi Vaziri

25:06.330 --> 25:08.637
inquiring
about the Soul of Genghis Khan,

25:08.681 --> 25:11.597
can I assume that
that's what you want me to find?

25:11.640 --> 25:13.903
Very good.

25:13.947 --> 25:15.818
Please.Thank you.

25:15.862 --> 25:18.386
Unfortunately,

25:18.429 --> 25:20.431
you led them to Russia.

25:20.475 --> 25:22.390
Now they have the upper hand.

25:22.433 --> 25:24.392
I gave them
incomplete information.

25:24.435 --> 25:26.829
Don't worry,
I can handle Danny and Lexi.

25:26.873 --> 25:28.962
Last time you faced them,
they beat you.

25:29.005 --> 25:30.529
Not really.

25:30.572 --> 25:32.182
They'd certainly have got
nowhere near Cleopatra

25:32.226 --> 25:33.270
if it wasn't for me.

25:33.314 --> 25:34.881
They've now entered Mongolia.

25:34.924 --> 25:36.578
The forbidden zone.

25:36.622 --> 25:38.101
My men followed them there.

25:38.145 --> 25:39.886
Oh, dear.

25:39.929 --> 25:42.453
My thoughts and prayers
to your men and their families.

25:42.497 --> 25:45.195
I once offered a lot of money
to some top-notch mercenaries

25:45.239 --> 25:46.457
to search out that area

25:46.501 --> 25:47.633
for the Banner.

25:47.676 --> 25:49.417
Only I never had to pay anyone

25:49.460 --> 25:51.550
because they never returned.

25:51.593 --> 25:53.813
Then it will serve as a grave

25:53.856 --> 25:55.858
for McNamara and Vaziri.

25:55.902 --> 25:58.295
Not necessarily.

25:58.339 --> 26:00.863
They're quite a formidable pair,
those two.

26:00.907 --> 26:03.823
I wouldn't underestimate them
if I were you.

26:05.259 --> 26:09.916
Well, for now, rest.

26:09.959 --> 26:13.180
And enjoy yourself.

26:13.223 --> 26:14.964
Thank you.

26:15.008 --> 26:18.533
A Khan shares his fortunes
with those loyal to him.

26:20.100 --> 26:23.756
But failure is met with death.

26:23.799 --> 26:26.106
HARDWICK:
No need for threats.

26:26.149 --> 26:27.716
I'm your man.

26:30.676 --> 26:34.201
♪

26:59.748 --> 27:01.750
Oh, no.

27:08.322 --> 27:09.932
[whispers]:
Here.

27:12.543 --> 27:15.155
[exhales]

27:15.198 --> 27:17.636
Hey.

27:19.768 --> 27:24.164
[exhales]
Look, I don't want to jinx us,

27:24.207 --> 27:26.253
but I really...I know.

27:30.518 --> 27:32.346
We're not dying today.

27:51.626 --> 27:53.672
[helicopter blades whirring]

27:58.851 --> 28:00.287
♪

28:23.484 --> 28:24.833
Now!

28:34.800 --> 28:36.540
Stick to the plan!

28:38.455 --> 28:39.718
DANNY:
Don't! It's a trap!

28:39.761 --> 28:41.197
Stay back!

28:41.241 --> 28:42.677
[groans]

28:45.375 --> 28:46.986
[grunts]

28:56.647 --> 28:58.824
[bird cawing]

29:09.965 --> 29:12.489
[indistinct shouting]

29:17.233 --> 29:19.192
[shouting continues]

29:23.805 --> 29:25.676
[grunting]

29:31.813 --> 29:33.641
We can't stay here.

29:33.684 --> 29:35.382
I'll draw their fire.
You find

29:35.425 --> 29:37.776
another way out.[shouts]

29:37.819 --> 29:40.387
[grunts]

29:40.430 --> 29:42.215
Do it! Go!

29:55.750 --> 29:58.100
[grunting, panting]

29:59.101 --> 30:01.712
Go. Get Danny.

30:01.756 --> 30:04.019
I'll hold them off for you.You're a sitting duck.

30:04.063 --> 30:06.587
My future is gone,
but you still have yours.

30:08.328 --> 30:10.373
[speaking Russian]

30:14.813 --> 30:17.119
[exhales]

30:46.801 --> 30:48.324
♪

31:17.658 --> 31:19.616
♪

31:49.385 --> 31:51.648
Danny!

32:01.354 --> 32:03.051
[hollow thudding]

32:12.278 --> 32:14.889
[grunting]Danny!

32:14.933 --> 32:17.457
Oh, God.Oh.

32:17.500 --> 32:19.763
I thought you were dead.

32:19.807 --> 32:21.330
I thought you
were dead.

32:21.374 --> 32:22.723
Come here.

32:22.766 --> 32:24.812
[both panting]

32:26.031 --> 32:28.294
I love you.

32:29.251 --> 32:31.819
We're surrounded.

32:37.781 --> 32:40.045
I love you, too.

32:50.446 --> 32:52.492
♪

32:56.452 --> 32:59.978
[horses neighing]

33:05.418 --> 33:08.421
Uh, Danny?

33:16.777 --> 33:18.474
Our situation

33:18.518 --> 33:20.999
does not seem
to have improved.

33:22.957 --> 33:25.655
Lexi, drop the gun.

33:25.699 --> 33:27.831
I feel like I should.Mm-hmm.

33:27.875 --> 33:29.833
And yet...

33:29.877 --> 33:31.879
If they wanted to kill us,

33:31.922 --> 33:34.229
we'd already be dead.

33:35.404 --> 33:36.449
Fair point.

33:36.492 --> 33:39.017
[exhales]Okay.

33:40.018 --> 33:41.671
Here.

33:45.675 --> 33:48.026
I saw one of these guys
back at the lab.

33:48.069 --> 33:50.724
Hopefully, he got
that we're not with them.

34:01.778 --> 34:05.260
I think that's his way of
saying we're free to go,

34:05.304 --> 34:07.088
but don't come back.

34:09.786 --> 34:11.223
Great.

34:11.266 --> 34:13.007
Works for me.

34:19.057 --> 34:20.493
Thanks.

34:21.929 --> 34:24.323
You didn't want to get involved
in spy stuff before...

34:24.366 --> 34:26.847
I definitely don't want to now.

34:26.890 --> 34:27.848
No freebie.

34:27.891 --> 34:29.241
Since when?

34:29.284 --> 34:31.460
Since you called
my mother crazy.

34:37.118 --> 34:39.033
[sighs]

34:41.253 --> 34:43.907
VINCE:
All right.

34:43.951 --> 34:45.344
Just tell me.FATHER CHUCK:
Thank you.

34:45.387 --> 34:46.997
This is from Kate.

34:47.041 --> 34:50.784
This is a letter to the CIA
from the 1960s.

34:50.827 --> 34:53.047
It's about the next steps
in something called

34:53.091 --> 34:55.615
Operation Temuüjin.Mm-hmm.

34:55.658 --> 34:57.530
And look. "The Spirit Banner

34:57.573 --> 35:00.576
"is in the hands of A.G.

35:00.620 --> 35:03.188
They will handle
future operations."

35:03.231 --> 35:05.277
And the whole thing
is stamped

35:05.320 --> 35:09.194
with the coat of arms
of the Holy See.

35:09.237 --> 35:13.328
Somebody high up inside
the Vatican sent this letter.

35:13.372 --> 35:15.765
A.G.? Who's that?

35:15.809 --> 35:18.420
I have no idea.

35:18.464 --> 35:20.596
Maybe it's the name
of somebody who knows

35:20.640 --> 35:22.642
why the Vatican
was attacked.

35:22.685 --> 35:25.123
Someone who's hiding
what's going on.

35:26.167 --> 35:29.170
I've given my life
to this church,

35:29.214 --> 35:30.432
and they could be lying

35:30.476 --> 35:32.565
about why my friends
were killed

35:32.608 --> 35:34.175
and why I almost was.

35:34.219 --> 35:37.613
[sighs]
Chuck, I used to be a cop.

35:37.657 --> 35:39.224
[clears throat]
A good one.

35:39.267 --> 35:41.748
It was the only thing
I ever wanted to be.

35:43.228 --> 35:47.536
For a while, I looked the other
way when I saw corruption.

35:47.580 --> 35:50.757
Figured it's not my problem,
I just keep my head down.

35:50.800 --> 35:52.976
And I saw how
the rot spread.

35:53.020 --> 35:54.935
How the good ones
turned bad,

35:54.978 --> 35:57.720
how the bad ones
got promoted.

35:58.721 --> 36:02.638
So, eventually, I quit.

36:03.596 --> 36:06.468
Well, so, you're saying
I should leave the priesthood?

36:06.512 --> 36:09.558
I'm saying organizations
rot from the inside out,

36:09.602 --> 36:12.170
and good people
try to stop it.Exactly.

36:12.213 --> 36:13.606
That's why I got
to do something.

36:13.649 --> 36:15.651
I didn't mean it as
a challenge, Chuck.

36:15.695 --> 36:17.479
I meant it as a warning.

36:17.523 --> 36:20.526
Because the good people
don't always win out.

36:20.569 --> 36:23.355
Sometimes they get
ground up and spit out,

36:23.398 --> 36:25.922
and everything else
just goes on as normal.

36:25.966 --> 36:29.230
Dude, that's so cynical.

36:30.927 --> 36:32.755
Well, you just keep
doing your priest thing,

36:32.799 --> 36:34.322
I'll do my P.I. thing.

36:34.366 --> 36:36.411
FATHER CHUCK:
What if I keep asking questions

36:36.455 --> 36:37.847
and I don't like the answers?

36:37.891 --> 36:40.198
You're a pretty good bartender.

36:48.771 --> 36:50.469
By the way,

36:50.512 --> 36:53.646
I meant what I said
back there.

36:53.689 --> 36:55.822
So did I.

36:55.865 --> 36:58.259
Levchenko was a nutter,
but he was right.

36:58.303 --> 37:01.088
It does change things.

37:01.131 --> 37:04.222
Well, get used
to hearing it more.

37:05.223 --> 37:07.573
Well, let's...

37:07.616 --> 37:09.314
spread it out a bit.
We don't have to go overboard.

37:09.357 --> 37:12.491
Yeah. Yeah, we don't
want to be thatcouple.

37:12.534 --> 37:14.101
Nah.

37:15.058 --> 37:17.191
[horse neighs]

37:23.153 --> 37:24.764
They've been
watching all along.

37:26.983 --> 37:28.681
All right.

37:28.724 --> 37:31.597
You get the credit
for that one.

37:31.640 --> 37:34.643
Come on. Let's go
before they reconsider.

37:34.687 --> 37:36.732
Yeah, I'll get
the truck started.

37:44.174 --> 37:46.786
Thank you.You're welcome.

37:55.621 --> 37:57.579
I gather from that expression
that I was right

37:57.623 --> 38:00.103
about the body count
in the forbidden zone.

38:01.061 --> 38:02.889
[chuckles]:
Do I also glean

38:02.932 --> 38:05.892
that Danny and Lexi
somehow managed to survive?

38:05.935 --> 38:09.548
Yeah. Yeah,
they're lucky like that.

38:10.984 --> 38:13.421
Maybe you'd like some help
adjusting your strategy.

38:13.465 --> 38:17.077
I know you think yourself
very clever, Mr. Hardwick.

38:17.120 --> 38:19.775
Always holding your cards
close to your chest.

38:19.819 --> 38:22.822
But those cards
cannot be played

38:22.865 --> 38:25.564
if I slit your throat.

38:25.607 --> 38:27.566
Go on!Uh...

38:28.523 --> 38:32.527
Now, convince me
why I shouldn't.

38:32.571 --> 38:34.224
Actually, if...

38:34.268 --> 38:36.662
If I could just have a
little space to recall?

38:36.705 --> 38:38.707
No? Okay, then. Fine.

38:38.751 --> 38:40.579
Uh, well, the man who hired me

38:40.622 --> 38:42.363
to search for your Banner
a while back

38:42.407 --> 38:44.104
is a rich financier.

38:44.147 --> 38:46.411
Arthur Chen.

38:46.454 --> 38:49.370
You got the same interests. He's
obsessed with the Great Khan.

38:49.414 --> 38:53.113
Fact is, my trail went cold,
and he went quiet.

38:53.156 --> 38:55.028
I...

38:55.071 --> 38:57.987
I always thought
that perhaps he found it.

38:58.031 --> 39:00.773
Where is this man?Hong Kong.

39:00.816 --> 39:03.210
And you withheld this
from your friends?

39:03.253 --> 39:06.126
Danny and Lexi didn't ask,
so I didn't tell them.

39:12.567 --> 39:15.614
I'd say the information I've
just given you earns my keep.

39:15.657 --> 39:17.572
[chuckles softly]

39:17.616 --> 39:19.835
I've just put you
ahead of the game.

39:19.879 --> 39:21.446
This is no game.

39:27.887 --> 39:30.150
You know, I found
something interesting

39:30.193 --> 39:32.805
